nkf
------------------------------------------
Nkf is a yet another kanji code converter among networks, hosts and terminals.
It converts input kanji code to designated kanji code such as ISO-2022-JP,
Shift_JIS, EUC-JP, UTF-8 or UTF-16.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.11.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.31.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  http://nkf.osdn.jp/

Canonical download:
  http://jaist.dl.sourceforge.jp/nkf/70406/nkf-2.1.5.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack nkf-2.1.5-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./nkf-2.1.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/nkf-2.1.5-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/nkf-2.1.5-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(nkf)
  /usr/bin/nkf.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/nkf.README
  /usr/share/doc/nkf/CHANGES
  /usr/share/doc/nkf/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/nkf/INSTALL.j
  /usr/share/doc/nkf/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/nkf/nkf.doc
  /usr/share/man/man1/nkf.1.gz

